I took computational metallurgy from her. The content was worse than undergrad metallurgy course. Had no use of any sort of computation, all theory. She is not compliant at all. If you really wanna learn something don't take this course.
Has a very good knowledge of the course and his excellent at teaching the course material to the students. Definitely recommended. Her exams are fair and lectures are worth attending.

Lecture notes are trash and lecture PPTs are even worst. Write and write from the board. There is not even discussion in the lecture. No clear definitions, no explanation of fundamentals and inadequate answers to questions. Exams are easy if you can cram the lecture notes. Must attend the lectures for notes (only!).

Dr. Bano is an underrated prof in the department. She is a little strict, but that is needed due to the giant mass of rambunctious students who often choose her classes. It is essential to write down everything she puts on the board, plus what she says in class, and go to lecture. There are no tricks in this class. Fair marker.

Attending her classes his really important, because the slides she uploads contain mostly theory. Everything important she writes on the chalkboard in class, which is why her notes are essential for quizzes, midterm and final. In my experience her notes are a mess with no structure. Therefore, studying for exams can be quite frustrating.
